ry.ts` - InventoryRepository managing stock (setStock, getStock, reserve, release, clear)\n- `/workspace/src/inventory/service.ts` - InventoryService listening to order events to manage stock reservations\n\n**Billing Module** (`/workspace/src/billing/`):\n- `/workspace/src/billing/calculator.ts` - calculateOrderTotal function computing subtotal, discount, tax, total\n- `/workspace/src/billing/service.ts` - BillingService handling payment charging and refunds\n\n**Notifications Module** (`/workspace/src/notifications/`):\n- `/workspace/src/notifications/service.ts` - NotificationService sending order confirmations, cancellations, and refund notices\n\n**Main Export** (`/workspace/src/`):\n- `/workspace/src/index.ts` - Public API exports (EventBus, ORDER_EVENTS, Order types, OrderService, InventoryService, BillingService, NotificationService, calculateOrderTotal)\n\n### 3. TEST FILES (5 files in tests/)\n\n- `/workspace/tests/events.test.ts` - 5 tests for EventBus (emit, multiple handlers, handler removal, clearing)\n- `/workspace/tests/orders.test.ts` - 13 tests covering OrderService lifecycle and OrderRepository operations\n- `/workspace/tests/inventory.test.ts` - 6 tests for stock reservation, release, and concurrency\n- `/workspace/tests/billing.test.ts` - 7 tests for payment calculation and charging\n- `/workspace/tests/notifications.test.ts` - 4 tests for notification sending and tracking\n\n**Total Test Coverage**: 30+ visible tests covering the full order lifecycle\n\n### 4. PACKAGE.JSON CONFIGURATION\n\n```json\n{\n  \"name\": \"bench-debug-nightmare\",\n  \"version\": \"1.0.0\",\n  \"description\": \"Event-driven order processing system — hard debugging benchmark\",\n  \"type\": \"module\",\n  \"scripts\": {\n    \"build\": \"tsc\",\n    \"lint\": \"eslint src/ tests/\",\n    \"test\": \"vitest run\"\n  },\n  \"devDependencies\": {\n    \"typescript\": \"^5.4.0\",\n    \"vitest\": \"^2.0.0\",\n    \"eslint\": \"^8.56.0\",\n    \"@typescript-eslint/parser\": \"^7.0.0\",\n    \"@typescript-eslint/eslint-plugin\": \"^7.0.0\"\n  }\n}\n```\n\n### 5. ARCHITECTURE OVERVIEW\n\n**Event-Driven Flow**:\n1. `OrderService.createOrder()` → emits `ORDER_EVENTS.CREATED`\n2. `InventoryService` listens and reserves stock → emits `ORDER_EVENTS.STOCK_RESERVED`\n3. `BillingService` charges payment → emits `ORDER_EVENTS.PAYMENT_CHARGED`\n4. `NotificationService` sends confirmation\n5. `OrderService.cancelOrder()` → emits `ORDER_EVENTS.CANCELLED`\n6. `InventoryService` releases stock → emits `ORDER_EVENTS.STOCK_RELEASED`\n7. `OrderService.refundOrder()` → emits `ORDER_EVENTS.REFUNDED`\n\n**Key Constraints**:\n- Orders must be in 'confirmed' status to cancel\n- Refunds only allowed within 30-day window (>= 30 days rejected)\n- Stock reservation is atomic with rollback on failure\n- Global event handler registry shared across EventBus instances\n\n**Configuration Files**:\n- `tsconfig.json` - Strict mode, ES2022 target, Module Node16\n- `vitest.config.ts` - 10-second test timeout, globals enabled\n- `.eslintrc.cjs` - TypeScript ESLint with strict rules\n- `.gitignore` - Standard Node.js ignores\n\n### 6. ALL SOURCE FILES SUMMARY\n\nTotal source files: **10 TypeScript files**\n- Events: 2 files (types, bus)\n- Orders: 2 files (repository, service)\n- Inventory: 2 files (repository, service)\n- Billing: 2 files (calculator, service)\n- Notifications: 1 file (service)\n- Index: 1 file (main export)\n\nThe system implements a complete order processing pipeline with event-driven architecture, supporting creation, confirmation, cancellation, and refund operations with stock management and payment processing."},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a230e89 (for resuming to continue this agent's work if needed)\n<usage>total_tokens: 31383\ntool_uses: 25\nduration_ms: 25413</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"e141cc80-3331-4895-86bf-0129d28ed448","uuid":"90624a5a-3c58-4082-a95d-2fb3f5122cc3","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt"